{"id":"e2f8ed0b-7bff-4902-ae29-49d13356910c","title":"1553/05/20: To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"46570903-1899-4a2c-995a-fee1364f6677","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, May 20th, 1553.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"15b8fd36-2a65-4c65-a73f-db9519b7ee50","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":3,"value":"8532f2fa-b614-4eed-9eae-586327f6a15a","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"fcedb4cf-c857-4473-a5d9-44ab9aff2ca5","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"bea2dbe8-07f4-4236-95c7-b4f91c91a7b9","type":"codex/time-reference","start":11,"end":24,"value":"b4345d00-027e-4c27-a25c-80cf4938c230","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c6cd24da-9d78-4a2e-bcb1-96996a67d76f","type":"style/superscript","start":17,"end":18,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"c7620740-619c-473b-990f-22554ed63d79","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"7b95f600-5726-49d7-ae23-15b8230ef61d","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"16611c54-a1ba-4f89-a645-2bf7cb54bd76","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"d4b2523e-89dd-4966-83db-e8270e17d29a","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"f1bfd09f-a3bb-49dc-9129-a0ba6088b763","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":1,"value":"0c663cc2-dd9f-40ce-b17b-734e41b369ef","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"da5906aa-8a78-4a1c-bcb0-6c4f0d7e4014","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"aa6169f8-df2d-4d14-ba1a-9cdf8f753ec4","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"c4f823ab-2b35-41e4-be8c-b6b4cd25a2d3","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0From thy last letter I learn that thou hast taken thy wife home and art well pleased with her: also, thou greetest me in her name and sayest that thou hast not as yet given security for the dowry. Thy satisfaction is a source of very great pleasure to me and I think we ought to thank God unceasingly with all our powers. As to securing the dowry, since thou hast not already done this hold thy\u00A0hand and keep thine eyes open, for trouble always arises from these money matters. I do not understand much about it, but I should suppose all these\u00A0things ought to have been settled before the bride went to thy house. As to thy greetings in her name, thank her on my behalf and make her a suitable reply by word of mouth, for I should not know how to make\u00A0one in writing. I should like it to be realised that she is the wife of one of my brother\u0027s children, however, but hitherto I was not able to give any proofs because Urbino had not then returned. He came back two days ago, and I shall now be able to demonstrate the\u00A0relationship. I have been told that a fine string of\u00A0valuable pearls would be a suitable gift. I have\u00A0accordingly instructed a friend of Urbino, a jeweller, to find me one and I hope he will be successful: but\u00A0do not tell her anything about it for the present. If\u00A0thou wouldst rather I gave her something else, let me know. I have nothing to add. Take care of thine own life; be considerate and thoughtful, for there are always more widows left in the world than\u00A0widowers.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"cc3b0ebf-a747-4fae-88cf-0fe90542beb5","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":7,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"a64f6848-e7d3-42a9-b69e-95483ecad3b4","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b